    <section name="Create custom compound">
     <span class="shortdesc">How to create a custom compound</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=450;
   </script>
   <div class='group'>
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_T07/inars/create_custom_compound.png" alt='Create custom compound'/>
    </div></div>
    <p>
     You create a custom compound just like a normal document type.
     Just add fields e.g. a <a href='./add_boolean_to_documenttype.html'>boolean field</a>.
     This is a compound called 'keys' that contains three primitive fields:
     Audience (letters), Difficulty (number) and On homepage (check button).
    </p>
   </div>

   <p>Make your custom compound available for use in document types or other custom compounds
      by <a href='update_all_content.html'>update all content</a>.
  </p>

